text: Tellis of Sicyon was an ancient Greek athlete listed by Eusebius of Caesarea as a victor in the stadion race of the 18th Olympiad (708 BC).Eusebius of Caesarea, Chronicle . He was the first winner from Sicyon. == References == == See also == Olympic winners of the Stadion race Category:Ancient Olympic competitors Category:Sicyon Category:8th-century BC Greek people Category:Ancient Sicyonians
title: Tellis of Sicyon
